            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "We present 'significance analysis of interactome' (SAINT), a computational agent that assigns confidence scores to protein-protein interaction data generated using affinity purificationg-mass spectrometry (AP-MS). The method uses label-free quantitative data and constructs separate distributions for true and false interactions to derive the probability of a bona fide protein-protein interaction. We show that SAINT is applicable to data of different scales and protein connectivity and allows transparent analysis of AP-MS data. © 2011 Nature America, Inc. All rights reserved.",
